@node INTRO
 @{b}Introduction@{ub}

  @{b}PswdGui@{ub} is a password protection program to be placed in your
  User-Startup or Startup-Sequence to prevent unauthorised access to your
  Amiga. It supports multiple Usernames and is supplied with a utility
  to change or add a new username and password.

    It was written using the fabulous Amiga E on my A1200 to stop certain
  members of my family gaining access to it.
@endnode

@node REQUIRE
 @{b}Requirements@{ub}

 - You require Workbench 2.04 or greater (Kickstart V37)
 - Reqtools.library V38 or greater (Not supplied!!!!)

   This has been tested on :-
   An A1200 with 2Mb of Ram and a 170Mb Hard Drive,
   An A600 with 2Mb of Ram and an 80Mb Hard Drive, 
   Two A500+'s with 1Mb of Ram each

 So it should work and if it doesn't don't blame me
@endnode


@node INSTALL
 @{b}Installation@{ub}

  - Copy @{b}PswdGui@{ub} To wherever you want.
  - Add an Assign to Pass: in your Startup-Sequence or User-Startup, this
    is where your Usernames will be stored.

  e.g. ASSIGN PASS: S:

  - Place the command PswdGui anytime after this.

  - Create a Username!! @{"Creating Username" link CREATE}
  
@endnode

@node CHANGEPSWD
 @{b}Changepswd@{ub}

All this simple little utility allows you to do is to add usernames
and passwords. It is a very simple utility to use and does not require 
a Rocket scientist to get it working. @{"Creating Username" link CREATE}

@endnode


@node CREATE
 @{b}Creating a Username and password@{ub}

   - Run the utility ChangePswd and input your Username and Password

   - Your Username can be a maximum of 20 characters and your password
     can also be a maximum of 20 characters

   - A file will be created in Pass: containing an encrypted version
     of your password.

     *** The password stored is case sensitive ***

   - If you want to change your password just input your username in the
     Changepass Utility and then your new password in the password box.

@endnode

